             Cephaluss message is that they should act like Sophocles rather than acting as they do. He wants us to infer that although ones character will not retard the advance of old age it makes old age less unpalatable, but his most important point is to turn the tables on his kinsmen, and this is what he means by saying that character helps against mudslinging. In short, the character in question is an impertubable smoothness which might, and probably will, be mistaken for moral competence.
